Package: BayesianStatisticalIntervalsCalculator
Title: BSI is a Bayesian Statistical Analysis Tool
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Ekin", "Ören", , "Ekin.Oren@Sanofi.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: BSI is a Bayesian statistical analysis tool that calculates and visualizes statistical intervals and posterior predictive distributions from uploaded MCMC output data. Users select fixed effects and variance components, defining a Linear Mixed Model in order to generate credible, prediction, and tolerance intervals with adjustable confidence levels.
